## ⚠️ CRITICAL: 유효성 검사 에러 메시지 구조

**MUST ALWAYS use the correct DOM structure for validation error messages when:**

- ✅ Creating new registration/edit forms
- ✅ Adding validation to existing forms
- ✅ Refactoring form components
- ✅ Ensuring UI consistency across forms

**MUST ensure error messages are placed INSIDE the inner wrapper div, NOT outside the field container.**

---

## 🏗️ 올바른 구조 (CORRECT Structure)

**MUST use this exact structure for all validated input fields:**

```tsx
<div
  className="register-form-mobile-field w-full md:w-3/4 flex items-center"
  style={{
    border: "1px solid #dee2e6",
    borderLeft: "none",
    borderTop: "none", // First row: remove this line
    padding: "5px",
  }}
>
  <div className="w-full">
    {" "}
    {/* ✅ Inner wrapper - REQUIRED */}
    <input
      type="text"
      name="fieldName"
      className={`w-full border rounded-none px-3 py-2 ${
        errors.fieldName ? "border-red-500" : ""
      }`}
      style={{
        border: errors.fieldName ? "1px solid #dc3545" : "1px solid #e0e0e0",
      }}
      value={formData.fieldName}
      onChange={handleInputChange}
    />
    {/* ✅ Error message INSIDE inner wrapper */}
    {errors.fieldName && (
      <div className="text-red-600 text-sm mt-1 px-2">{errors.fieldName}</div>
    )}
  </div>
</div>
```

**Structure Diagram:**

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
│ register-form-mobile-field          │ ← Field container with w-full md:w-3/4
│ w-full md:w-3/4                     │
│  ┌──────────────────────────────┐  │
│  │ w-full (inner wrapper)       │  │ ← REQUIRED inner wrapper
│  │  ┌────────────────────────┐  │  │
│  │  │ input                  │  │  │
│  │  └────────────────────────┘  │  │
│  │  [error message]             │  │ ← Error message INSIDE
│  └──────────────────────────────┘  │
└─────────────────────────────────────┘
```

---

## ❌ 잘못된 구조 (WRONG Structure)

**MUST NOT use this structure:**

```tsx
<div className="w-full md:w-3/4">
  {" "}
  {/* ❌ External wrapper - WRONG */}
  <div
    className="register-form-mobile-field w-full flex items-center"
    style={{
      border: "1px solid #dee2e6",
      borderLeft: "none",
      padding: "5px",
    }}
  >
    <input
      type="text"
      name="fieldName"
      className={`w-full border rounded-none px-3 py-2 ${
        errors.fieldName ? "border-red-500" : ""
      }`}
      style={{
        border: errors.fieldName ? "1px solid #dc3545" : "1px solid #e0e0e0",
      }}
      value={formData.fieldName}
      onChange={handleInputChange}
    />
  </div>
  {/* ❌ Error message OUTSIDE field container - WRONG */}
  {errors.fieldName && (
    <div className="text-red-600 text-sm mt-1 px-2">{errors.fieldName}</div>
  )}
</div>
```

**Why this is WRONG:**

1. ❌ Error message is outside the field container, breaking layout consistency
2. ❌ Responsive design issues on mobile devices
3. ❌ Visual disconnect between input field and error message
4. ❌ CSS styling becomes unpredictable

