# Form Field Component Usage Rules

## ⚠️ CRITICAL: Reusable Form Field Components

**MUST ALWAYS use shared form field components from `@/shared/ui/adminWeb/form` when:**

- ✅ Creating new registration/edit forms
- ✅ Refactoring existing forms
- ✅ Adding new form fields to existing forms
- ✅ Ensuring UI consistency across all forms
- ✅ Building any admin web form (member, board, code, program, etc.)

**MUST NOT:**

- ❌ Create custom form field markup structures
- ❌ Duplicate form field HTML/CSS code
- ❌ Use inline form field styles directly
- ❌ Mix custom markup with component-based approach

**Why This Rule is CRITICAL:**

1. **Code Reusability**: Single source of truth for form field implementation
2. **Consistency**: All forms use identical UI/UX patterns
3. **Maintainability**: Update once, apply everywhere
4. **Type Safety**: TypeScript interfaces ensure correct prop usage
5. **Reduced Bugs**: Standardized components reduce styling and logic errors
6. **Developer Experience**: Faster form development with pre-built components

---

## 🧩 Available Form Field Components

### Component Library: `@/shared/ui/adminWeb/form`

**MUST import from the shared form component library:**

```typescript
import {
  FormField,
  FormInput,
  FormSelect,
  FormTextarea,
  FormRadioGroup,
} from "@/shared/ui/adminWeb/form";
import type { SelectOption, RadioOption } from "@/shared/ui/adminWeb/form";
```

### Component Overview

| Component | Purpose | Props |
|-----------|---------|-------|
| `FormField` | Field wrapper with label and container | `label`, `required`, `isFirstRow`, `isFirstInRow`, `fullWidth`, `error`, `children` |
| `FormInput` | Text input fields (text, password, email, tel, date) | `name`, `value`, `onChange`, `error`, `type`, `placeholder`, `maxLength`, `readOnly`, `disabled`, `className` |
| `FormSelect` | Select dropdown fields | `name`, `value`, `onChange`, `options`, `error`, `loading`, `loadingText`, `emptyText`, `disabled`, `required` |
| `FormTextarea` | Multi-line text input | `name`, `value`, `onChange`, `error`, `placeholder`, `maxLength`, `readOnly`, `minHeight` |
| `FormRadioGroup` | Radio button groups | `name`, `value`, `onChange`, `options`, `error` |

---

## ✅ CORRECT: Using Form Field Components

