# Form Layout and Button Consistency Rules

## ⚠️ CRITICAL: Form Layout Consistency

**MUST ALWAYS use the standard 2-column layout pattern when:**

- ✅ Creating registration/edit forms
- ✅ Adding fields to existing forms
- ✅ Refactoring form layouts
- ✅ Building any admin web form (member, board, article, code, program, etc.)

**MUST ensure ALL registration/edit forms use consistent 2-column layout across the entire application.**

**Why This Rule is CRITICAL:**

1. **Visual Consistency**: All forms must look identical in layout structure
2. **Space Efficiency**: 2-column layout maximizes space utilization
3. **User Experience**: Consistent layouts reduce cognitive load for users
4. **Professional Appearance**: Inconsistent layouts look unprofessional and untested
5. **Maintainability**: Standardized layouts are easier to maintain

---

## ✅ CORRECT: Standard 2-Column Layout Pattern

**MUST use 2-column layout for registration/edit forms:**

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT: 2-column layout pattern
<div className="flex flex-wrap">
  {/* First row: Field 1 (left) + Field 2 (right) */}
  <FormField
    label="Field 1"
    required
    isFirstRow
    isFirstInRow
    error={errors.field1}
  >
    <FormInput ... />
  </FormField>
  <FormField
    label="Field 2"
    isFirstInRow
    error={errors.field2}
  >
    <FormInput ... />
  </FormField>
</div>

<div className="flex flex-wrap">
  {/* Second row: Field 3 (left) + Field 4 (right) */}
  <FormField
    label="Field 3"
    error={errors.field3}
  >
    <FormInput ... />
  </FormField>
  <FormField
    label="Field 4"
    isFirstInRow
    error={errors.field4}
  >
    <FormInput ... />
  </FormField>
</div>
```

**Layout Rules:**

- ✅ **Two fields per row**: Each row should contain two fields (left and right)
- ✅ **Complex fields**: Even complex fields (date range "from ~ to", file inputs, etc.) should be in left column with another field in right column
- ✅ **Full-width fields**: Only textarea or description fields can span full width using `fullWidth` prop
- ✅ **First row**: First field uses `isFirstRow` and `isFirstInRow`, second field uses only `isFirstInRow`
- ✅ **Subsequent rows**: First field has no special props, second field uses `isFirstInRow`

---

## ❌ WRONG: 1-Column Layout (Inconsistent)

**MUST NOT use 1-column layout unless absolutely necessary (e.g., full-width textarea):**

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG: Each field in separate row (1-column layout)
<div className="flex flex-wrap">
  <FormField label="Field 1" isFirstRow isFirstInRow>
    <FormInput ... />
  </FormField>
</div>
<div className="flex flex-wrap">
  <FormField label="Field 2">
    <FormInput ... />
  </FormField>
</div>
<div className="flex flex-wrap">
  <FormField label="Field 3">
    <FormInput ... />
  </FormField>
</div>
```

**Why this is WRONG:**

1. ❌ **Inconsistent with other forms**: MemberRegisterForm, BoardRegisterForm all use 2-column layout
2. ❌ **Wastes vertical space**: Unnecessarily uses more screen space
3. ❌ **Visual inconsistency**: Creates confusion when navigating between forms
4. ❌ **Unprofessional appearance**: Looks like incomplete or rushed implementation
5. ❌ **Even complex fields should use 2-column**: Date range, file inputs, etc. can be left column

**Common Mistake Example:**

**Real-world case: ArticleRegisterForm**
- ❌ Used 1-column layout for all fields
- ❌ Reason: Thought date range field "from ~ to" needed full width
- ❌ Reality: Date range field can be left column (50%), status field can be right column (50%)

**Fix:**
```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT: Date range in left column, status in right column
<div className="flex flex-wrap">
  <FormField label="게시기간" error={errors.ntcrStartDt || errors.ntcrEndDt}>
    <div className="w-full flex items-center gap-2">
      <FormInput type="date" name="ntcrStartDt" ... />
      <span>~</span>
      <FormInput type="date" name="ntcrEndDt" ... />
    </div>
  </FormField>
  <FormField label="상태코드" isFirstInRow error={errors.sttusCode}>
    <FormRadioGroup ... />
  </FormField>
</div>
```

---

## ⚠️ CRITICAL: Form Action Button Consistency

**MUST ALWAYS use consistent button text, position, and order for ALL registration/edit forms:**

**Standard Pattern (MUST follow exactly):**

1. **Button Order**: Register/Submit button (LEFT) → Close button (RIGHT)
2. **Button Text**: "등록" / "등록 중..." → "닫기" (NOT "취소")
3. **Button Colors**: Blue (`bg-blue-600`) for 등록 → Gray (`bg-gray-500`) for 닫기
4. **Button Classes**: Standard classes with `minWidth: "100px"`

**Why This Rule is CRITICAL:**

1. **UI Consistency**: All forms must have identical button patterns
2. **User Experience**: Users expect consistent button placement and text
3. **Professional Appearance**: Inconsistent buttons look unprofessional
4. **Accessibility**: Consistent patterns help users navigate faster
5. **Prevent Mistakes**: Standard pattern prevents common implementation errors

---

## ✅ CORRECT: Standard Button Pattern

**MUST use this exact pattern for ALL form action buttons:**

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT: Standard button pattern for registration/edit forms
<div className="flex justify-end mt-3 gap-2 px-6 py-4">
  <button
    type="submit"
    className="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded hover:bg-blue-700 disabled:bg-gray-400 disabled:cursor-not-allowed"
    style={{ minWidth: "100px" }}
    disabled={loading}
  >
    {loading ? "등록 중..." : "등록"}
  </button>
  <button
    type="button"
    className="px-4 py-2 bg-gray-500 text-white rounded hover:bg-gray-600"
    style={{ minWidth: "100px" }}
    onClick={handleCancel}
    disabled={loading}
  >
    닫기
  </button>
</div>
```

**Required Properties (MUST use exactly):**

- ✅ **Button order**: 등록 (left) → 닫기 (right)
- ✅ **Button text**: "등록" / "등록 중..." (when loading) and "닫기" (NOT "취소")
- ✅ **Button colors**: `bg-blue-600` for 등록, `bg-gray-500` for 닫기
- ✅ **Button classes**: `px-4 py-2 rounded` with `minWidth: "100px"`
- ✅ **Container classes**: `flex justify-end mt-3 gap-2 px-6 py-4`

