## 💡 Key Principles

1. **Consistency First**: ALL registration/edit forms MUST use identical layout and button patterns
2. **2-Column Standard**: Always use 2-column layout unless full-width textarea
3. **Reference Before Implementation**: Always check existing forms before creating new ones
4. **Primary Action First**: Primary action (등록) should be left, secondary (닫기) should be right
5. **Standard Text**: Always use "닫기" (not "취소") for close button
6. **Visual Verification**: Always compare visually with existing forms after implementation
7. **Complex Fields Fit**: Even complex fields (date range) can use 2-column layout

